# probability_smoke.numos — open the Probability app, screenshot, and ASSERT it is active.
#
# Phase 6A smoke test. ProbabilityApp is LVGL-native and emulator-safe: it pulls
# only lvgl + ui::StatusBar + input/KeyCodes + KeyboardManager + a pure <cmath>
# ProbEngine (no Giac/CAS, no LittleFS/Preferences, no heap_caps/PSRAM, no
# sensors/WiFi). This script opens it through the emulator-only `open_app` command
# (added in Phase 5A: it calls the SAME NativeHal launchApp() the launcher uses, so
# it is deterministic and does not depend on fragile grid navigation), captures a
# screenshot, and asserts the active app is "Probability".
#
# The app opens with default normal-distribution parameters mu=0, sigma=1, x=0
# (sigma=1 != 0, so the bell-curve PDF/CDF compute has no division-by-zero). As
# with every emulator screen, the only volatile region across runs is the StatusBar
# clock (HH:MM). This phase makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for
# human review only.
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash (~frame 125) is done; we are in the launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Probability screen load + fade settles after open_app.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/probability_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/probability_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "probability_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Probability (emulator launchApp id 5 — same id as the launcher's Probability card).
open_app Probability
wait 60

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/probability_smoke.ppm
log "probability_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Probability
log "probability_smoke: assertion passed (Probability active)"
